 present were cautious at first, their guards had their weapons ready.  Two wizards, present, however took the young Teir'Dal in and sheltered them.  Ironically, one of them was the guild's leader.  When the guards protested, the leader ordered them to return to Takish-Hiz and report it to the king if they held a problem with his decision.  The guards did just that.<br><br>The wizards quickly learned that their sheltered Teir'Dal was a fellow wizard.  This discovery broke down several of the barriers of mistrust, but not all.  When the time came for them to confirm their dedication to Solusek Ro, the Teir'Dal joined them.  The discovery that a hated enemy followed Solusek Ro removed the racial barriers.  The Teir'Dal was welcomed among the Koada'Dal worshippers.<br><br>Eventually, however, the guards did make their report.  The king sent out an legion to arrest to the Teir'Dal and disband the wizard guild.  Ro was gracious to the wizards, and when the legion finally arrived, the Teir'Dal was not to be found.  Even the wizards were puzzled.  The legion departed, not completing their orders, with beliefs that the guards of the guild were drunk.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> II. Plasmatic Priesthood</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Solusek Ro grew angry with the Koada'Dal for their attack against the Teir'Dal he sent.  The flames of sun reached toward Norrath, creating a draught.  As the land dried up, small fires began in the forest.  The druids began to combat Solusek Ro's magic and summoned great storms to combat the draught.  It seemed as if the Elves might survive Solusek's curse.  But his magic would be so easily defeated.<br><br>Solusek sent visions to the wizards of the guild that housed the Teir'Dal.  When they awoke, they met in council to discuss the dreams.  Shortly after, they formed the Plasmatic Priesthood, which is now known for its worship of Fennin Ro.  The Priesthood travelled among the Elddar Forest, spreading the warning of Solusek.  Most considered them drunken fools and disregarded their warnings.<br><br>Realizing the futality of trying to teach their heathen brothers, turned to subvert the druidic efforts the counter Solusek's efforts.  Whisking away a group of clerics, the Preisthood travelled to Hills of the Serpent.  Channeling the awesome powers of Solusek Ro in conjuration with the cleric's Earthquake spell, the the hills arched upwards, creating the Serpent Mountains.  The heat exhausted in the effort banished the rain storms the druids summoned.<br><br>Angered with their actions, the crown sent the entire Koada'Dal army out to drive the Preisthood out from the Elddar Forest.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> III. The Flaming Spear of Solusek Ro</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Solusek Ro grew tired of toying with the Elves of Tunare.  He had given them plenty of chances to change their ways.  Conjuring up a great firestorm, Solusek Ro swept away the forest of the Elves.  The city laid open before the armies of the Teir'Dal.  As the armies of Innoruuk approached, Karana summoned a squall to give the Koada'Dal time to flee.<br><br>Solusek Ro grew angry with Karana and his actions.  As the armies of Innoruuk came closer to the city of Takish-Hiz, Solusek Ro finished his curse.  Hefting his great Spear of Flame, Solusek Ro herled it into the heart of the the Elven Empire.  The burning flames created a great current in the air and the squall of Karana was blown away.  The raging flames engulfed the land and the sea retreat, creating a vast and barren desert.  The invading Teir'Dal army was completely destroyed along with the Koada'Dal warriors who stayed behind to combat the Teir'Dal army.  Feir'Dal druids fled with their kin to the lands of Butcherblock to avoid the flames.<br><br>What remained of Takish-Hiz was turned into the Deserts of Ro, serving as a reminder to the Elves of their mistake.<br><br>-Ikeya <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% v